
Picking a Duress code, tree simple qualities first;
Easily remembered, even after months of non-use.
Easily entered in stressful moments, but not easily butt/pocket-dialed.
Ease of discerning from all your other pins, passwords and pass phrases.

Picking a Duress code, The extra mile;
A fourth property could be added as desired regarding a good Duress pin slashplus password. This would be picking a Duress code with the aim of it being sufficiently 'passphrase-like' in the eyes of an adversary so that they actually would try it on your confiscated device. Imagine that your Duress code is 1526, and you find yourself not able to type it in time and your adversary now grabs your device. You say the unlock pin is 1526. This may be too 'Duress-like' for the adversary to 'swallow as a bait'.
